==English==
===Adjective===
'''unbroken'''

#Whole, not divided into parts.
#:''After the vase had fall down the flight of stairs we were amazed to find it still '''unbroken'''.''
#Describing a [[horse]] that has not been tamed.
#:''There is something majestic about the spirit of an '''unbroken''' Mustang as it runs wild across the prairie.''
#Continuous, without interruption.
#:''The team's '''unbroken''' winning streak was a record.''